caption: I live around the same area and I love their food omg. I usually order from door dash and this has been the one spot that serves hot/fresh food. Im satisfied after eating a little bit. Thank you so much Darbar! I'll wait till five pm for your delicious food lol
Amazing food and service.
Every time the food is excellent. If you don't want to come inside they will come to you outside and hand you your order. Really nothing more I could ask for them to do better! Thank you all!
Such a good experience, our waiter was so kind and thoughtful. The food was excellent. I wouldn’t hesitate to go back.
The best Indian food in the area with the absolute best service!! Must visit. Even better when you eat inside.
So good! They made adjustments for our kid's tastes, and still burned me out with the extra spicy vindaloo. Highly recommend trying it out!  Edit to clarify: I WANTED it that hot. It was perfect!
Amazing food and great service! Definitely try out their lamb saat and chicken tikka masala.
Very delicious! Authentic Indian food, incredible flavors, and the service was wonderful.

Hidden gem! Our first love is Indian Food and we were not disappointed. Amazing service, high quality safety, and the food. Delicious! Our 8 yo crushed a paneer tikka and garlic naan. My chaat, mulligatawny soup, and olive and basil naan was exactly what I have been craving. Husband ordered chicken tikka. Fantastic! Spice levels were spot on. Thank you for a pandemic treat!

The experience and service were wonderful and the food was great! I highly recommend chaat for an app the flavors are phenomenal. The naan is delicious and the tikki masala is so great! Worth a visit for sure!

One of the best Indian restaurants in Baltimore. Amazing chaat, tandoori, naan, everything they have is delicious and freshly prepared and the service is fantastic and extremely attentive, I highly recommend this Baltimore gem.
Great food great service

Amazing spot, best Indian food in the city. Service impeccable even on a Wednesday night with a complimentary drink! We also order takeout often. Once, Uber eats messed up and cancelled my order and the owner brought it to my residence on his own. It’s a mistake to miss out Darbar <3

Darbar is one of the most consistently good restaurants in Baltimore. Super reliable. Living nearby, it hits the spot for a midweek meal in the dead of winter or those late summer dinners. Miss visiting for deals in person since covid, but their carry out has been so prompt, attentive, and always friendly. The owner and his family are truly good people and makes it all the better to support a local place.
Excellent restaurant! Service is great, very attentive. Food is delicious! Will be coming back.
Incredible food and impeccable service. You really can’t ask for a better experience. If you’ve never been, consider this your final push to get you through their door. You won’t regret it.

Really good food!! The palak tiki was top class! The mango chutney pairs well with this dish. The breads were tasty too. The kadai paneer was lip smacking good. Just the way it would be in India. The host was very warm and welcoming. The food came out relatively quickly. For the quality of the food and service the food is very reasonably priced. I’m sure I’ll be coming here again.
Great hospitality ! Very clean & spaced out. Love the saag  & vindaloo! Trio basket of breads is so great so you get to try them all! Cannot wait to go back!
The food was tasty definitely a great starter place for those who have never had the cuisine and I loved the garlic Naan bread
Absolutely delicious food every time - one of my go to’s for weekend takeout!
The best Indian food it is absolutely fantastic! Go to this place, period!
Great service. Put DARBAR on the map. 🚀
totally amazing foods
We just love this place! They give great recommendations when asked. Great food and friendly service- not to forget very clean as well! Can’t recommend enough.

TOTALLY RECOMMENDED, MUST TRY!! The service was excellent and the food was delicious. Went with my mom and we both loved it. The portions were hefty, so we got to eat the yummy leftovers the next day. We were even treated to a glass of wine and a lovely dessert on the house!! Thanks to the host and staff.

We had a wonderful birthday celebration for my husband’s  birthday at Darbar!  Our server gave us amazing recommendations that were spot on.  After our delicious meal, we were treated to a delightful gulag jamun birthday special.  You must give Darbar a try!
Excellent Indian Food!  Each dish had its own unique spice blend and haven't found a bad one yet.  Medium is pretty spicy for the American palette... Hot is good, but watch out! ;)
very good indiana food!
The food is regularly well prepared and delightful, staff members provides excellent service. I liked how clean it is and ambience. Would recommend to others.
We just had an EXCELLENT meal!  Some of us are vegan, I called and he talked through what we could eat and they prepared the saag so it could be vegan. Fast too.

Great service! Even modified a dish for me. Total social distancing tonight as we have the place to ourselves. Glass of wine on the house. I'll update after eating.  Food was amazing! The meat samosas are excellent and the roti!  Just like mom's cooking.  Will be getting take out in the near future.  Definitely recommend
Everything is always perfect, great food and drinks and excellent service! Highly recommend.
Excellent meal and service by Mir. Plenty of menu options, food delicious and Mir made some great recommendations. Will definitely be back.
I visit this spot a lot since I work close by. I have to say the customer service is always fantastic and they keep the place clean constantly. Rates are convenient and they serve generous portions.
Fantastic service, wonderful place to grab great wine, awesome food, and delicious desserts! Will be back again.
The butter Chicken was out of this world. Prompt service too!

Pretty good food and awesome customer service. Got lamb vindaloo and butter chicken, not the best, but also not the worst, good enough. Mango lassi, bread and crab sticks were awesome and everything was fresh. Also saw few $5 vodka based cocktails in menu, sounds fun. Interior definitely needs some renovation, there was missing chandelier on the wall, just 2 wires sticking out and water stain on the carpet, paintings, colors, textures and overall atmosphere were good. Our waiter was really good guy who took good care of us.

This is authentic and highly recommended restaurant. Good Indian fusion and also customizable per your taste buds. The staff/chef is very knowledgeable and has met my expectations consistently. For those who prefer authentic spices and hot, just ask for "desi style" ;) Ambiance and hospitality at its best! Best Indian restaurant in the area.

What a wonderful dinner at Darbar! My daughter and I had a wonderful dinner. So authentic. Plus, they can make things the way you like. My daughter wanted a plain llasa, not the mango. They served up a sweet, or a salty. The portions are huge, and so good. I had the goat curry. My daughter had a spiced chicken with sauce on the side. Basically, you can't go wrong. I love Indian food. I've dined there before, but this was definitely worth a review. DARBAR! on Aliceanna & Wolfe Sts in Fells Point. Yum.
I believe it was the owner, but very nice and respectful. Trying his very best, consistently checking up on us. Food amazing. Great experience, recommend.
Food was amazing, very nice host. Definitely will come back.

The host was immediately friendly and welcoming. We enjoyed having the complimentary glass of wine. The food here is absolutely delectable. The Punjabi Samosa Chaat off the appetizer menu was AMAZING- I can’t rave about it enough. The flavors were complex and delicious and I’m dying to have it again. We also had the lamb vindaloo which was tender and spicy in a good way. Their mango lassi was one of the best I ever had. Can’t wait to come back to Baltimore and visit again!!
The lamb Tikka Masada was amazing! The service was spectacular. I will definitely be back to support this small business. 😁
Terrific food, service and prices, can't beat Darbar for a great dining experience in Baltimore
Very friendly helpful and great food
Everything was fantastic! The food is always so delicious that we order twice as much as we need, just to be sure there are lots of leftovers.
Great food. Great price 👍👍👍
Amazing, great food, great service! Complimentary wine with our delicious meal. Highly recommend, best Indian food in the Fell’s/Canton area.

Great food and a friendly, cozy atmosphere. I've tried a lot of different chicken tikka masala and this one is definitely on the sweet side but it was nice to have something a little different. The flavors all melded together perfectly.
Medium Spice Okra is delish
I admire this restaurant very much. It has a friendly spirit. The kitcen is wonderful. the service is efficient and the personel is trained. The pay is modest. profoundly recommend.
Loved everything, from the service to the food!!!!

First time visiting the area and stopped by here for dinner because my sister was craving Indian food. 2 of us are also Vegan and they were very accommodating. Service and food was great! Definitely recommend!!
Awesome and friendly service
Delicious
1st time eating Indian food. The food was excellent. The service was great!. Will denfintly return.
I had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here.
Went for lunch today September 29. The food and service was excellent and the wine was wonderful.
Have only done takeout from Darbar.I love the the chicken Tiki Masala.
Everything was delicious! Service was incredible and friendly. Highly recommend for both dine-in and carry out.

My husband and I went out for a walk and decided to stop at Darbar for dinner. I’m so glad we did. Since it was our first time, we each decided to try several dishes. He ordered the Aloo Gobi and Indo Veggie Fried Rice. I had the Malai Kofta and Dal Makhni. All of it, including the Garlic Naan and Raita, was delicious! Plus, we had plenty left over for lunch the next day. Great service, great food…we’ll definitely go back.
the food was great, but the company was even greater. my sincerest compliments to the chef <3
Great experience! The waiter was very kind and the food was amazing! 10/10
Great food and great service.  A very good value.
Looking forward to returning with my coworkers. Prices were average for the menu.
i see why this place has a lot of good reviews.

Instantly the host was amazing. He was very welcoming and friendly and the restaurant decoration was elegant. There were many menu options and selecting something was difficult because everything looked good. I don’t like spicy and my boyfriend does, and they were able to make our food perfectly for each of our preferences. Everything was delicious! I’m looking forward to eating the leftovers and eating there again to try other menu options.

Incredible food and flawless service. They made extra accommodations for us to sit outside and then adjusted last minute for a friend to join. Our waiter, Mir was so accommodating. So happy to have such incredible Indian food so close to home!

The garlic naan we ordered was very small round thin and burnt. It should be fluffy and the size should bigger. These guys try to cut conners  where the saving is not significant. I don’t think we are going to patronize this place again.
Interesting menu. We wished our take out was a little hotter. It seemed kind of bland.
Food was BANGIN' son! Trust meeeeeeee!!!!!

Amazing experience here! The food was absolutely delicious! Our main dishes, appetizer, and naan bread were all so yummy. We were also offered a complimentary glass of wine. We were able to sit at a nice outdoor table and our waiter was mindful of social distancing and wore a mask the entire time. Our service was fantastic. Our waiter was prompt and super friendly. He gave us wonderful recommendations about which dishes to try and accommodated all requests. We will definitely be returning here to eat many times!

We were so hopeful with this place being a couple blocks away but we were sadly disappointed. The sauce tasted like ketchup surprise and the chicken korma had spice but VERY little flavor! The rice was super dry and flavorless. We also order the garlic naan and the garlic was dry garlic flakes. If you want great Indian food order from Mt. Everest in Hampden.
Very nice people

Service was excellent.  So thorough and attentive that I felt a little guilty for being treated so well!  The food was excellent.  Spice level just where I hoped it was.  I could eat the naan every day for the rest of my life.  Thanks for being one of the restaurants open for business during this difficult time.  We got pushed off by a number of other places before we found you.
Great food and service!

Tasty food, I went with the Lamb Rogan heat 6.  Probably could have gone with more.  It got the sweat beads poppin though.  Garlic Naan was on point.  The service was great and attentive.  Portion size was perfect, not to much and too little.  I will back again.  Maybe next time I will go for dessert, but with pools opening back up I am trying to get back to my thong weight.  Give Darbar a shot you'll be glad you did.

The place is not gaudily advertised. I was unsure of what to expect. Upon arriving, our server was prompt and would have kept stuffing us with baskets of maddeningly addictive papadum. Our food was delicious with a slow building spice that keeps you going back for more. The fact that there were no raisins in the biryani alone deserves a star. Service was great and the atmosphere very condusive to conversation.
Definitely order the Punjabi samosa chaat—it’s sweet with heat. And the Darbar Chicken curry was another wonderfully full flavor.

We have tried their weekend buffet a few times, and each visit left us with a food coma - tasty food, decent service, okay ambiance, relaxed environment. We usually go for a walk by the water in Fells or Canton after our meal here.
Great customer service. Food is delicious.
Bar-none, the best Indian food in Fells Point!

Omg!!!!! I love Indian food but this restaurant makes it to PERFECTION! I ordered delivery so I don’t know what the restaurant looks like but my food came VERY NEATLY PACKED!!!! Everything was neatly done OMG!!!!! If I could give you more than five stars I would!!!! Very few restaurants have met my expectations but this restaurant exceeded my expectations. Thank you very much for your service!!!!
Incredible food. Just a fair warning: Medium spice is probably a bit too spicy (both “hot” and “lots of spice”) for people not accustomed to spicy food.
The food is really fresh and apt amount. The taste is really good and spice levels are awesome. Vegetarians also have good options

The absolute best Indian food in Fells Point! The samosa chaat app is insanely delicious. We love the Tikka masala and the vindaloo, as well as the naan! The service is always excellent too, whether we're dining in or taking out!
Great budget indian buffet.  Really attentive service.
Great authentic indian food experience!
Garlic naan was superb, and I loved the main entree. The service was top notch. Highly recommend!
The food is really good. Especially the Lamb dishes like Lamb Biryani and Lamb Curry.
Loved the food. The lamb curry was really tasty and the lamb biryani was absolutely delicious with lamb beautifully cooked.

Great food. Great service. Will be back!!! I'm especially thankful for the birthday cake with a candle they brought out for me and put on an instrumental happy birthday music track on the sound system when they brought it out. Very nice surprise and classy execution. Thank you! :D
Friendly staff. Very helpful and communicative about the different dishes on the menu. Overall some of the best Indian food we’ve had in Maryland. 10/10 would def recommend.

Incredible service and the food was also awesome! Everything came out quickly. I have a hard time with spicy food but love Indian food and was able to order my favorite dish without any spicy heat. It was awesome and can’t wait to come back!
Had Indian food here during stay at Baltimore. Excellent Authentic India Dishes with great service & taste.Must try for all fan of Indian food.
In terms of flavor, this is the best Indian food in East Baltimore! Tasty chicken tikka masala and saag. Highly recommend the lunch buffet. Hidden gem.
This is a gem place in the city. Limited options yet tasty. Food is not spicy for folks concerned about that. Feels like home food!

It's a quiet restaurant that does a fair amount of take out business, not a lively crowd inside. None of that matters though because their food A-mazing. I went with a group of friends and we ordered 5 different dishes between us, they were all superb. The butter chicken and lamb tikka masala were to die for. I've been dreaming of the lamb since I finished the last of it as leftovers earlier today. Easily the best Indian food between Canton and Fells.
Helpful staff!  Great food. Samosas with tamarind are great!
Loved the food and services, must visit.

We just visited darbar restaurant for first time on the way to nj to Florida it's 14th Feb and they also had lots of orders but still there service was very nice special thanks naved's service and staff was really helpful and food was really amazing. Must visit.

I wasn’t a big fan of Indian food and hadn’t had any in a long time. That changed today at Darbar. My waiter was AWESOME the food was fantastic and the restaurant was in clean and pristine condition. I ordered buttered chicken hot and it was out of this world. My waiter continually offered to help explain any dishes or recommend if necessary to us. Anyone who doesn’t rate this place a 5 is out of their mind....I cannot wait to return and try some of their other dishes...beyond impressed with everything

We enjoyed a delicious dinner here.  I’ve been to India twice and this food is definitely authentic!  The service was courteous and attentive, and the complementary glass of wine was a bonus.  We’ll definitely come back!

Went a couple weeks ago for the first time with a friend. Great experience! The server was super helpful and knowledgeable of the menu items. I highly recommend asking for their suggestions. I'm no stranger to Indian cuisine, but it never hurts to ask what the staff like. Was not disappointed, and I tried something new!! There is a lot of consideration for spiciness level, and there are options for everyone depending on preference. Hope to be back soon!
Probably one of the best Indian food restaurants in the city.
The first shout out goes to the excellent customer service and the second goes to the excellent Indian food, which tastes like it was cooked by an Indian Mom.
Love the new Management the waiter had good customer service.
Great buffet and prompt service.
Just perfect. The service, the food, and the environment. Highly recommended for those who want to try Indian cuisine.

Went with my son last night....we were there as they opened (5pm)....greeted and seated by the owners brother as if he were welcoming us into his home. The food was DELICIOUS....and he presented it with pride but also with caring as to our opinion of it. Food and service 5 stars....cleanliness 5 stars...he even brushed off crumbs between courses....will definitely go back....often!

Went here on my birthday and had a great time! Service was wonderful and the food was delicious. All meals come with complimentary wine and I also got a free birthday treat which was special. Will be back soon!
I had ordered veg soup and chicken soup, that was delicious, loved that, and mr Mir was fabulous. He had done great job to take and deliver my order.

We had a great experience here on a Saturday afternoon. We ordered from the menu. The waiter was quite helpful in guiding us in response to our questions. I've eaten in many Indian restaurants. The food at Darbar ranks at the top!
The best India food in usa
Good service 👍
Good food and service
The food is delicious, the service is awesome, and the prices are very reasonable.
Outstanding food and service...A+

We are a large group and love dining at Darbar! The staff are so nice, always so accommodating and really go the extra mile. When not sure what to order their recommendations are spot on and the food is delicious with generous portions.  I also highly recommend the lunch buffet!  Love tasting a wide variety of dishes at a very good price. Thank you Darbar, we’ll be back again very soon! Wishing you all the best and Happy New Year 2020!
Great food and service. We went there on Christmas Eve with 9 people and had a wonderful evening.
Nice Indian cuisine but needs a spicy heat level option.
Great service and the chicken tikka masala is not to be missed! So glad we finally ran into this place.
Food was not good
Great place to eat... great service...
Smells terrible
Wonderful food and service!!!
The food and service was exceptional.  I'll be back
We had an awesome experience, the food was AMAZING, service was excellent, and soooo worth the price! Highly recommend
Amazing food!

Was visiting Baltimore and looking for a good Indian restaurant. This place was recommended by my Uber driver and was happy that I took his suggestion to have dinner here. Friendly staff with authentic and tasty food. Our waiter was very accommodating of our choices and was very helpful in suggesting the right dishes to suit us. Had a great time to satisfy my desi taste buds!!!

This place is around the corner from my house and is the first place I ate when my family moved to Baltimore. That was six months ago, and we've returned to Darbar many times in that span. The food is on par with that of the best Indian restaurants I've had in different cities. The service is impeccable. I highly recommend it!
The staff was so plesant and the food was delicious, our experience here was the best!
Neat and clean restaurant with high quality, spicy Indian dishes
Favorite Indian food in the city! Great service, atmosphere and very delicious!

We had a celebration dinner at Darbar last night - the food was delicious and the service wonderful!  There was an abundance of delicious food and we had some to take home.  I have one suggestion though - the food would fare much better if transported in a sealed container as opposed to a styrofoam carrier. We had a lot of waste as it wound up leaking into the bag.  We will be back!

Absolutely brilliant! I wish I could give 6 stars!  My partner and I visited on 10/23/19 and were blown away. The service was fantastic, great atmosphere and best of all, the food was incredible!  We were provided with a complimentary glass of wine and starter papadums, and each entree was served with a free (and large) serving of rice. We ordered samosas for starters, then the Chicken Tikka Masala and Lamb Korma for entrees; superb. The serving sizes were well and truly large enough for the two of us, with leftovers to spare, and the eventual cost was cheaper than a standard bar dinner.  We have recommended this to our entire network in Baltimore and as we live locally in Fells Point, we will certainly be visiting again! Definitely recommend for anyone looking for great food at a good price, with excellent service; support local!

My daughter and I loved Darbar!  #1 is the excellent staff, they truly do care that their customers have a great meal and a special time at their restaurant.  Several pleasant surprises throughout the meal, plis great food and a very nice atmosphere... What more could anyone want?
Excellent food, waiter who knew the menu inside and out, exceptional service.
Perfect value for money

Oct-5-2019: We were visiting a friend new to Baltimore.  Andrew found Darbar knowing that we like Indian buffets.  Most of my family prefers mild spice.  While some may prefer heat, my wife said that this was her favorite Indian food ever.  She was happy that there was a lot of flavor without being too spicy.  The cost for our daughters; 12 and 7 was very generous!  Naan was available on the buffet, but Darbar delivered fresh plain and garlic naan to our table. Andrew ordered take out for his fiance.  Later that evening he sent a text saying that she enjoyed her lunch very much and there was enough for the two of them to share for supper. Totally recommend Darbar anyone wanting to try Indian food for the first time and for families with a range of spicy hot tolerance. Great flavor, generous portions and nice casual atmosphere.
Excellent food in an unassuming environment. Or second time here and I already can't wait to come back. Service is exceptional to boot

Excellent authentic Indian food! And great service for being an Indian restaurant! If you are in the area must go! Water refills without asking, constant check backs, really feel valued guests! Thank you team Darbar! Keep up the great work!!
The menu and service were ahead of my expectations. We absolutely loved the ambience of this spot. Fantastic spot to take the family out for lunch.
Mir was extremely polite Very good service and food was delicious. Will visit soon.
great food, great service!
Currently this is the best Indian restaurant in the city -- and it's not close.

The food and service was amazing here! Highly recommend it to anyone looking for some tasty Indian food. The restaurant was very well put together and our server was very attentive to us. Best Indian cuisine in Baltimore!
Great food combined with very attentive service made for a great experience.
Great lunch very friendly staff

I visited yesterday with friends and  I had an amazing time.  Everyone was extremely polite and  very wonderful to be around.   I was celebrating my birthday.  The food was wonderful and the staff went above and  beyond giving me a cake!  I can not recommend Darbar enough!
Really good food good service

Just finished dinner here and it was honestly one of the best Dining experiences I’ve ever had. The waiter treated us like we were important family and dinner featured complimentary wine and dessert. The food was authentic and delicious. The suggestions made by our waiter were all amazing and I felt like we really got a taste of authentic food and hospitality. We’re going to be back soon, for sure!
Good is always delicious and service is great.  Definitely recommend to everyone.
Delicious food, they took our togo order 15 minutes before closing. They were really polite

The staff was excellent and the food was that and more. The server recommended the samosas chaat to the regular veggie samosas and it was spectacular, definitely an upgrade. They cut the samosas open and add garbanzo beans, yogurt sauce, tamarind sauce, and mint sauce over the top!! I had the Aloo Gobi and my partner had the Chicken Tikka Masala and both were delicious with the garlic naan. I can't wait to go again soon. Oh and they gave us a free dessert that was so yummy!
Amazing food, great price
Great buffet!

Darbar never disappoints! Not only is their food fresh but they change their types of food all the time. The naan is always delicious and made fresh daily. I am limiting my meat intake and Darbar is the perfect place for me since they always have a lot of vegetarian options. The veggie broth soup and the chai tea are just some of my favorite things here. The service is also exceptional and the atmosphere is calming. We will definitely be back!
Amazing food. Great variety of vegetarian dishes with depth in flavor. Best vegetable pakora ever! Check out the buffet on the weekend, it's the perfect variety.
Delicious Indian food at an affordable price

Darbar is Joyful, Delicious and On-Point!  Stellar Service: from the moment you walk in, you feel welcomed and well take care of. They will walk you through the menu and offer insights.  Stunning Food: The flavors, the portions, the colors, the seasoning... it was AMAZING! Everything was timely, perfectly executed and full of flavors. [We had chicken plates (Malai & Masala; 2 different broths) and Nan (garlic & cheese-stuffed).]  Darbar iz cozy and playful. We had a peaceful dinner while they played instrumental music in the background. Can’t wait to go back soon!
Very good food, the cleanest dining room and the nicest, most attentive host I have ever met. Great Dining experience!
Very nice food
The service is fantastic and everything is delicious. Even if it looks empty, GO.
Dinner was excellent - great quality food and really friendly and efficient service. Would definitely eat here again.
The food was amazing! Nice atmosphere.

I've been going to the lunch buffet for a year (cheap, delicious, vegetarian/vegan options!) and keep coming back. Today I went after work for the dinner menu and it was splendid. My friends and I had garlic naan, appetizers, a main course, dessert, and wine. Everything from service, atmosphere, food, and price was fantastic. Come to the Darbar and fall in love with Indian cuisine!
Delicious food, friendly service, and great recommendations! Will definitely be returning!
The food and service were great! We visited during buffet hours (which I highly recommend). There was a large variety of foods and many options for vegetarians.

Went for dinner and had a great experience. We'd heard there was a new owner and wanted to try it out after not having gone in a few years. The food was excellent and the service was great. We will definitely go again and recommend it to anyone interested.
Try dishes that don't have cream in it, they're amazing.
We found this place during our visit to Inner harbor. The food is very tasty.
Yummy food and great service.
Incredible service and better food! The waiter was accommodating and helpful to a vegan member of our party, and threw in a free dessert as well. Overall a great experience and we will be back.
Amazing food and service! Highly recommend!

The food was extremely unflavorful, even though we did not ask for mild food. we have had shahi paneer many times before at other Indian food restaurants and it has never looked or tasted like this. the sauce was watery, whiteish brown and flavorless except a slight taste of cheese that left a very unpleasant flavor in your mouth. Shahi paneer should be a tomato cream sauce with blocks of cheese and other indian spices but this was watered down and really unappetizing. unfortunately we had taken the food to go so we couldn’t return it and ask for something else.
Amazing buffet allows you to taste a lil of everything.  Great Service!
Great service and authentic Indian food. Highly recommended.
Amazing service! The waiter told us the restaurant is under new management, and everything was wonderfu!!

High quality food , good spot and a wonderful service . The waiter is no nice ! You can feel india’s spices made through each meal made with attention . A great place to get introduced to the Indian culture .
Authentic south asian cuisine. Very courteous people. One of the few halal options around The Fell's point
All you can eat buffet, Monday through Saturday. Good value
Not a big Indian food eater but they were soooo nice there
Absolutely fantastic experience. Really delicious food and wonderful service. We are so lucky to live nearby and will be returning frequently. Highly recommend!
Wonderful service, very helpful with ordering and helped us pick out some great dishes including the chicken mehti and lamb biryani.  Both were great.  I highly recommend!
Loved the food!!! Everything was delicious!! Mir, our server was very friendly and helpful. Highly recommend coming here!! One of the best spots in Baltimore; you need to stop by if you are in town.

I can’t say enough nice things about the food and the service. Probably the best saag paneer I’ve had. The staff was attentive without being overbearing and our server was excellent. I will definitely be back! Thank you, Darbar!
Friendly service.
Food was spot on and our waiter was so nice and knowledgeable. Went there for dinner, but definitely want to go back for their lunch buffet!
The best Indian food in town Not much else needs to be said Unless u never had Indian food before If you are going to try Indian food for 1st time I will recommend chicken tikka masala with naan
Great chicken vindaloo it's a bit spicy though, the goat curry is ok... the mango kulfi  is great!!! One of the better Indian places in Maryland
Food is good ... taste really nice. Worthy for what you pay.

The food is remarkably fresh and very well prepared. The owner (new) and server were very pleasant and personable. Their garlic naan was a revelation.  It's a bit off my usual beat, but I will definitely be going back.
Great food and service.  New owners, definitely a solid choice in Fells Point.  Tandoori choices are really good.
This is was my first time eating Indian food and they set the bar high. Service was amazing. Staff was fantastic. Highly recommended

I’ve only eaten Darbar through services such as Grubhub and Uber Eats.  I ordered this a couple months ago and at first bite, it was terrible. Instantly upset my stomach. Come to find out later, the other person who was eating with me didn’t feel so well either.  Last week I decided to give it another go, ordered the same thing I had ordered in the past. Ate a few bites, didn’t sit very well and soon after I was sick over a toilet. Would not recommend this to anyone. Spoke with some others and found that they also have been sick from here.
We enjoyed the hospitality and food Will surely recommend to all food lovers. Amar and shital.
Good food, good taste, good experience!!
Great food. We were there for lunch so it was a nice and quiet atmosphere. Try the mango lassi.
Good Food and service
Great experience all-around, delicious food and kind staff. Good for large groups.
I have visited many restaurants in Baltimore , but to me this one has the best buffet... I liked the chicken tandoori and I will be Back again for it And to try other recipes..
Coolest place and best food in Baltimore 😍😍😍
Good food. Friendly staff

I came here on the recommendations of my coworkers for the lunch buffet; it's a decently-reviewed local Indian restaurant not far from the office, what's not to like? Quite a bit apparently. Pull up to the restaurant and you're greeted by a small, non-assuming restaurant not akin to to a hole-in-the-wall. We walked inside, were promptly seated at a table, and dug into the buffet. Being Punjabi and having dined at Indian restaurants across the world, I typically have very high expectations for 1) the authenticity of the dishes 2) the preparation of the curries and 3) the quality of the tandoori dishes/breads. Given this, I lowered my expectations for Darbar-- sadly, they were still not met.  You've got a buffet that's on the small side, expect 5-7 main dishes, rice, and your usual accompaniments. A lot of the vegetarian dishes were made with cheaper substitute ingredients. For example, you've got mushroom kadai instead of paneer kadai (really?). The naan is not served alongside the buffet-- a huge drawback. Instead, small baskets of naan are brought to your table. We received 3 naans total (not nearly enough for 3 guests during a buffet). Not once did the serving staff or manager bring any more baskets. No guest should have to ask for more naan in a bottomless buffet--period. See my review of dishes below: ---- Things I Liked: Gulab Jamun - You can't really mess up Gulab Jamun, especially when it's store-bought like the jamun here.  Rasmalai- Ditto above.  Naan - The naan was just fine, but not nearly as fluffy and tandoorlike as it should be. 3/5  Things I Disliked: Vegetable Samosa - The veggie "samosas" in the buffet were NOT samosas. Instead, they were frozen veggie and potato patties that were fried and served in the buffet. These were not made in-house either, as I instantly recognized the frozen foods brand from which they were bought (I use them at home and they're available in Indian stores everywhere). Tasteless and overcooked, these patties were very poor. 1/5  Saag Spinach - Palak paneer (or saag) is a difficult dish to screw up. You've got cooked spinach, usually with some cream thrown in, and a base of tomatoes, onions, garlic, and ginger. This palak was bland and flavorless-- even paneer (if there was any) wouldn't help this dish. 2/5  Chicken Tikka Masala - Many people confuse butter chicken and chicken tikka masala. Butter chickenis meant to be light and sweet, while chicken tikka should be more tart and spicy. Unfortunately, I'm not sure Darbar's chicken tikka falls in either camp. The dish was too sweet to be chicken tikka but not nearly creamy enough to be butter chicken. Tough pieces of overcooked chicken dominate this dish with its watery curry. 2/5  Dal Makhani - With far too many lentils packed into this dish, the taste simply does not shine through. There is no evidence of a tomato, onion, garlic, and ginger base (tadka) and the dish lacks any buttery creaminess (makhan = butter/cream). 2/5  Tandoori Chicken - Typical of poor Indian restaurants, this chicken was far too dry and devoid of flavor. This is because the chicken had obviously been sitting in the buffet dishes for some time, being constantly heated and dried. The tandoori flavors simply did not shine past the initial bite of dry chicken. 2/5  I would not recommend Darbar; it might be okay for a quick fix but simply lacks the authenticity and careful preparation of dishes. The spices simply do not reveal themselves in any dish neither is the service or atmosphere worth nothing. While not in Baltimore, I would recommend the following Indian restaurants instead:  Royal Taj (Elkridge, MD off of 175 by Costco) Ananda (Fulton, MD off of 216 by Maple Lawn) Chutney (Columbia, MD off of Snowden River Pkwy) Rasika (2 locations in Washington, DC.) Indigo (H St, Washington, DC.)
